  "doc_id": "52848",
  "text": "Recidivism from violent injury is the critical long-term outcome in our hospital-based violence prevention program. In the 6-year period of our VIP (2005Y2011), 23 clients (9%) had been previously admitted to San Francisco General Hospital for violent injury before enrollment. Sixteen clients (6.2%) were reinjured after WAP services, 5 of whom had open cases with WAP case managers at the time of reinjury. These results translate to a current recidivism rate of 4.5%; the historical injury recidivism rate at our institution was 16%. [CITATION_1] ",
